description: Retrieves the origination settings for the specified Voice Connector.

nested_items.name: Routes
nested_items.description: The call distribution properties defined for your SIP hosts. Valid range: Minimum value of 1. Maximum value of 20. This parameter is not required, but you must specify this parameter or Disabled.

nested_items.name: Host
nested_items.description: The FQDN or IP address to contact for origination traffic.

nested_items.name: Port
nested_items.description: The designated origination route port. Defaults to 5060.

nested_items.name: Protocol
nested_items.description: The protocol to use for the origination route. Encryption-enabled Amazon Chime SDK Voice Connectors use TCP protocol by default.

nested_items.name: Priority
nested_items.description: The priority associated with the host, with 1 being the highest priority. Higher priority hosts are attempted first.

nested_items.name: Weight
nested_items.description: The weight assigned to an origination route. When hosts have equal priority, calls are distributed between them based on their relative weights.

nested_items.name: Disabled
nested_items.description: When origination settings are disabled, inbound calls are not enabled for your Amazon Chime SDK Voice Connector. This parameter is not required, but you must specify this parameter or Routes.
